<b>WORK EXPERIENCE</b><br />
<p>
West Chester University, Pennsylvania; Iowa State University, Iowa; California State University, Los Angeles
</p>
<p>
Mary’s professional experience includes over 10 years of work in the Student Affairs Division of the University including positions such as Director of Orientation and Leadership, Director of Student Organizations, Assistant Dean of Students and as a Faculty member with Freshman 101 course for undecided majors.  Through these positions Mary worked with the Admissions office in various capacities. She also worked as a counselor in the Career Planning and Placement Office as a Graduate Student.  Later in her university career, Mary moved into the Institutional Advancement Division and worked as an Executive Director of Alumni Relations and Annual Fund for 5+ years, raising money for college student scholarships and other important college programs.  Throughout her career Mary has traveled to over 130 institutions of higher education and has great knowledge about how to match a student’s interests, needs and abilities with the right college or university. There is a perfect college for everyone!  Her counseling experience definitely helps families work through the college admissions process so it is a positive experience!</p>
<p>
In her free time, Mary volunteers for her national fraternity, Alpha Chi Omega as President of the Foundation Board of Trustees.  This work helps to keep her informed with the latest trends on college campuses.  In addition, she keeps updated in the field by attending seminars, visiting campuses and researching published materials, newspapers, journals and magazines so we can provide the best and latest resources to our students. She is also a member of the Western Association of College Admissions Counseling.
</p>
<p>
Mary lives in Irvine California with her husband Bob, their son Andrew, who is in middle school and Katie who is a freshman at the University of Southern California studying Theatre Arts as of the Fall 2012.
