<p><b>WORK EXPERIENCE:</b></p>
Tufts University, Massachusetts; Northeastern University, Massachusetts; Endicott College, Massachusetts
</p>
<p>
Renée’s professional experience includes over 10 years of work in higher education with experience in the areas of Dean of Students, Student Activities, Admissions, Residential Life, Cooperative Education, and Athletics. She has also worked as a counselor in the Admissions and Career Planning and Placement Office as a Graduate Student. Her career and interests have been devoted to the world of higher education as well as working with high school students to help prepare them for their exciting futures. Renée has traveled across the nation to over 75 institutions of higher education to specifically assist her students in finding the many fantastic options available to them. </p>
<p>
Renée believes that the college admissions process should be an absolutely exciting adventure, an adventure that typically involves the whole family. Her mission is to reduce the stress and anxiety often associated with the college application process by assisting her students with discovering the many amazing higher educational institutions that match their talents and future aspirations.</p>
<p>
Renée’s previous experience as the Development Director of Lazarus House Inc., a homeless Shelter and Soup Kitchen located in Lawrence Massachusetts, the 24th poorest city in the United States, helped her realize the impact and value of community service and volunteering and is able to assist her students effectively match their passions with service opportunities as well. She is a member of NEACAC, New England Association for College Admission Counseling. Additionally, she keeps current in the field by attending national and regional admissions and higher education conferences and seminars, visits college campuses around the nation regularly, often meeting with admissions counselors and researches published materials, newspapers, journals and magazines so that CQA can continue to provide the best and latest resources to our students.</p>
<p>
Currently, Renée serves as a board member of the Pristash PTO Scholarship Committee with recent volunteer work on several boards such as the PTO committees at the elementary, middle and high school levels as well as the North Andover Youth Center fundraising committee. She is also a huge fitness enthusiast, especially devoted to the practice Bikram Yoga. Renée lives in North Andover, Massachusetts with her husband, Anthony Serrano, Tufts University, their three children, Ashleigh, Indiana University, 10’ majoring in Communications and Telecommunications and Northeastern University, M. ED in Higher Education and Administration; AJ, University of Southern California, 12’ Cinematic Arts, Film and Critical Studies, with minors in Business and Philosophy and Alexander “Bubba” who is currently in the Class of 2014 at Harvard University studying Film and Literature. 
